 Easter is almost upon us and this means that multitudes of  South Africans will be headed to far-off destinations to visit relatives or just to enjoy the holiday. With the increased traffic volumes on our roads, the chances of accidents increase and our emergency medical services need blood when they arrive at the scene of an accident. READ ALSO: Hope picnic in aid for cancer As a result, the South African National Blood Service (Sanbs) are on a drive to encourage citizens to donate blood in order to saves live during this period. Watch the video below for a message from the Nelspruit Sanbs :  READ ALSO: South African emergency services on way as Cyclone Idai nears Mozambique